<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <style>
    body { font-family: 'Rajdhani', sans-serif; padding: 2rem; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #222; }
    h1 { font-size: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid #444; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    h2 { font-size: 20px; margin-top: 2rem; }
    h3 { font-size: 16px; margin-top: 1rem; }
    .section { margin-top: 2rem; }
    .severity-Critical { color: red; }
    .severity-High { color: darkorange; }
    .severity-Medium { color: goldenrod; }
    .severity-Low { color: green; }
    .severity-Informational { color: gray; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 1rem; }
    th, td { border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 8px; vertical-align: top; }
    th { background-color: #f4f4f4; text-align: left; }
    ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
    .flex-row { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 2rem; }
    .chart { flex: 1; max-width: 300px; }
    .summary-points { flex: 2; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>AN3 – Smart Contract Audit Report</h1>
  <p><strong>Audit Date:</strong> {{ scan.created_at }}</p>
  <p><strong>Contract:</strong> {{ scan.contract_name or 'N/A' }}</p>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>1. Audit Methodology</h2>
    <p>This audit was conducted using both automated and manual review techniques. We utilized tools like <strong>Slither</strong> and <strong>Mythril</strong> for static analysis, and integrated AI-assisted post-processing to identify potential false positives and missed vulnerabilities. The methodology includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Static code analysis using Slither & Mythril</li>
      <li>Manual line-by-line inspection of contract logic</li>
      <li>Cross-verification against known SWC-Registry vulnerabilities</li>
      <li>AI-based validation for confirming the findings and identifying overlooked bugs</li>
      <li>Evaluation of best practices, design patterns, and known attack vectors</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Note: This audit does not guarantee the complete absence of bugs or vulnerabilities. It reflects the state of the contract at the time of review.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>2. Executive Summary</h2>
    <div class="flex-row">
      <div class="summary-points">
        <ul>
          {% for vuln in vulnerabilities %}
          <li class="severity-{{ vuln.severity }}">{{ vuln.severity }}: {{ vuln.issue }}</li>
          {% endfor %}
          {% for vuln in missed_vulnerabilities %}
          <li class="severity-{{ vuln.severity }}">AI-Detected {{ vuln.severity }}: {{ vuln.issue }}</li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="chart">
        <img src="{{ pie_chart }}" alt="Severity Chart" width="250">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>3. AS-IS Contract Overview</h2>
    <p><strong>Contract Name:</strong> {{ contract_logic.contract_name }}</p>
    <h3>Functions:</h3>
    <ul>
      {% for fn in contract_logic.functions %}
      <li>{{ fn.name }} — {{ fn.visibility }}{% if fn.payable %}, payable{% endif %}</li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>4. Detailed Findings</h2>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Severity</th><th>Issue</th><th>Description</th><th>File</th><th>Line</th>
      </tr>
      {% for vuln in vulnerabilities %}
      <tr>
        <td class="severity-{{ vuln.severity }}">{{ vuln.severity }}</td>
        <td>{{ vuln.issue }}</td>
        <td>{{ vuln.description }}</td>
        <td>{{ vuln.location.file or 'N/A' }}</td>
        <td>{{ vuln.location.line or 'N/A' }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
      {% for vuln in missed_vulnerabilities %}
      <tr>
        <td class="severity-{{ vuln.severity }}">{{ vuln.severity }} (AI)</td>
        <td>{{ vuln.issue }}</td>
        <td>{{ vuln.description }}</td>
        <td>{{ vuln.location.file or 'N/A' }}</td>
        <td>{{ vuln.location.line or 'N/A' }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </table>
  </div>
</body>
</html>